Japanese construction company Obayashi Corp. said  Thursday its pre-tax earnings dropped 18 percent from a year earlier to 57.7  billion yen (563 million dollars) in the year to March.
But the company said revenue rose seven percent to 1.63 trillion yen.
For the current year, Obayashi forecast an even smaller profit of 42  billion yen on lower sales of 1.45 trillion yen.
